      "identifier": "ERR_CFG_01",
      "summary": "Startup accepts invalid CLI port values silently by falling back to defaults.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/main.go",
        "goseg/config/config.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`parseStartupOptions` parses `--http-port` and `--ws-port` with `strconv.Atoi` and on conversion failure only logs an error while continuing; no error is returned to the main startup flow.",
        "The same function populates `listenAddr`/`wsAddr` from defaults after failed parsing, so invalid input can start a server on unintended ports without explicit operator feedback."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Return an error from `parseStartupOptions` for invalid user-supplied port flags and abort startup with a clear message; alternatively collect all parse errors and fail fast before listener startup, and keep the default path only when flags are absent.",
