      "root_cause_cluster": "inconsistent_error_contract"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "ERR_IMP_02",
      "summary": "Upload error handling can drop backend failures when a response has already been written.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/importer/importer.go",
        "goseg/importer/importer_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`failUploadRequest` returns errors via named propagation from response publishing/write operations.",
        "Callers guard handling with `if err != nil && !responseWritten`, so when `responseWritten` is true, upstream transport/publish errors are not surfaced through the same error path and are effectively downgraded to silent failure."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split the operation into explicit stages: write response status once, then independently handle/return backend-side failures via explicit logging + metrics + caller-visible error return; ensure both paths are tested (response-written and non-response-written) in `importer_test.go`.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "inconsistent_error_contract"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "ERR_WG_03",
      "summary": "Wireguard artifact write path applies different recovery strategies depending on filesystem read error class.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/wireguard.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/internal/artifactwriter/artifact_writer.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`WriteWgConf` first attempts `os.ReadFile` and only on `os.ErrNotExist` performs fallback behavior.",
        "For other read failures (e.g., permission or transient I/O), the function returns immediately without attempting the fallback write path that exists in artifact writer logic, resulting in inconsistent outcomes for equivalent failure intent."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Unify recovery semantics: on any read failure, attempt a bounded fallback path via `artifactwriter.Write` and include context-rich error wrapping so callers can distinguish source-read issues from generation/write failures.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "incomplete_fallback_strategy"
    }
  ],
